events.name: July Meetup: Programming Design Patterns

venue.name: HackerDome
venue.address_1: 2nd Floor - Vishwadarshan Complex, PU/4 Commercial 50, A.B Road Behind C21 Mall, Mega More, Malviya Nagar Indore, Madhya Pradesh

events.description:
Pre-requisites - Object Oriented Programming Concepts

Agenda : 

• What are design patterns

•  Background

• Typical application scenarios

• Types of design patterns

• Singleton, command, wrapper, adaptor, factory, decorator

-----

I/O 2015 Recap

-----

What all best practices to follow while programming a system?

Solution is "Design Patterns".

Design patterns can speed up the development process by providing tested, proven development paradigms. They are the solutions to general problems that software developers faced during software development. They represent the best practices used by experienced object-oriented software developers.

Design patterns are optimized, reusable solutions to the programming problems that we encounter every day. A design pattern is not a class or a library that we can simply plug into our system; it's much more than that. It is a template that has to be implemented in the correct situation. It's not language-specific either. Get understanding of design patterns background, where to user them, categories, and different types of implementation.

events.name: TensorFlow Dev Summit: Viewing Party

venue.name: Techcoopers Software Solutions
venue.address_1: Shekhar central

events.description:
Hello Indore,

“HackCoopers - An 18-hour Hackathon” hosted by TechCoopers where crazy ideas become reality.

Mark your calendars for the 16th and 17th of March and join us for this hackathon where collaboration is preferred over competing and everyone is equally welcome.
Venue: TechCoopers Pvt Ltd, 214 ,Shekhar Central, Palasia,Indore.

Discussions, fun, games, and learning will all be a part of this hackathon.

To Bring your crazy potential to reality, register for this hackathon at
http://bit.ly/hackcoopers-register

All teams must have either 3 or 4 members.

We're thrilled to announce that Google is hosting the TensorFlow Dev Summit which will take place on March 6-7, 2019 Google Event Center Sunnyvale, California USA.

GDG Indore is hosting an extended event for the same. We will watch the keynote, lightning talk and discuss the case studies presented at the TensorFlow Dev Summit.

We’re super excited to bring Google's latest Machine Learning offering - ‘Machine Learning Crash Course (MLCC)’ to Indore. This meetup is intended for those who wish to learn about ML from a practical, applied perspective that will enable them to use machine learning within their everyday projects, and who wish to benefit from the power of TensorFlow wrapped in convenient higher-level abstractions. This is a great opportunity for professionals, entrepreneurs, and students to gain some practical experience in ML and TensorFlow.

Website: https://www.tensorflow.org/dev-summit/

What? The Machine Learning Crash Course with TensorFlow APIs

This course will be suitable for you, if:
You are a strong programmer
Ideally, you are at least somewhat familiar with Python. You don't need to be an expert.
Ideally, you know at least a little about linear algebra and calculus.

Agenda:
http://bit.ly/2F1nKyq

Other requirements? Additionally, we’d need you to bring:
Your laptop and charger. You will need this to go through the online course.
Pen & paper (or any other preferable option if you plan to take notes)
A can-do attitude!
